column3: The video was filmed at night and shows elements of the Civil Defense while searching in the rubble in a place where some signs of destruction are visible, as it was allegedly targeted. It also shows the Civil Defense elements collecting what appear to be remnants of ammunition. The video contains testimony of a civil defense element about the incident.

column2: ALQUDS
column3: The video begins with footage that appears to have been recorded by one of the surveillance cameras inside what seems to be a medical point. The footage shows a corridor with curtains of a brownish color.  The place looks empty at first, then many people appear, one of them wears military trousers, and another wears a medical uniform. A man with a child in his arms, surrounded by a woman and several children, can also be seen. Another person can be seen wearing military trousers and carrying what appears to be a walkie-talkie. The video continues later, with footage recorded by another surveillance camera shows what seems to be the entrance to the medical center. Several people, including children, enter. We also can see people in medical uniform, a person with a camera, and someone wearing military trousers carrying a walkie-talkie and asking a child to go out to remove his clothes. The logo of "Free Aleppo Doctors Association" can be noticed on the wall on the right side near a number of cardboard boxes. The video continues with footage from the first surveillance camera again, where it shows a number of people in medical uniforms, women, children, people with a camera while filming.  A white cylinder and another blue one can be noticed. The video also shows a person in medical uniform distributing protective masks to everyone. Later, the footage appears to be filmed outside the medical point where a person in medical clothing washes someone with water. The video continues with footage from the first surveillance camera, and then footage appears to have been recorded in the same medical center according to the color-matching in the curtains, the presence of a white cylinder and a number of blue cylinders. A number of the injured can be seen with oxygen masks and people in medical uniforms While providing medical treatment to the injured. The video was filmed inside and outside of a medical point after the incident; It is a  merge of several clips, some of which were recorded by what appear to be surveillance cameras

column2: Targeting Al-Zabdiyah neighborhood with a barrel bomb contains chlorine gas
column3: The video shows a child stretched out on a bed in a medical center and seems to have died. It can be observed that he had been intubated. The video also contains testimony of someone who appears to be an injured, as he has been provided with an oxygen mask, and someone else's testimony about the incident.

column2: A woman and two children were killed as a result of bombing Al-Zabdiyah neighborhood with poison gas
column3: The video was filmed at night and shows elements of the Civil Defense while searching in the rubble in a place where some signs of destruction are visible, as it was allegedly targeted. It also shows the Civil Defense elements collecting what appear to be remnants of ammunition. The video contains testimony of a civil defense element about the incident.

column2: Injured civilians as a result of targeting Al-Sukkari neighborhood with chlorine gas
column3:
The video shows a number of injured who have been provided with oxygen masks, as well as medical staff members while providing medical treatment to the injured. The video was filmed in the same medical point that appeared in another video
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qvIJfktU71c
where the "Free Aleppo Doctors Association " logo can be seen on one of the medical point's walls.

column2: Targeting Al-Sukkari neighborhood with chlorine gas
column3: The video begins with footage appears to be from a civil defense vehicle as they were heading to the impact site. As the video continues, it shows people seem to be civil defense members in a neighborhood where the signs of destruction are visible and heavy dust can be seen in the area. After that, the civil defense elements appear near a building seems to have been recently attacked and a car appears to have been hit as signs of destruction are visible in the street near it. Then the video shows a red car seems to be used to transfer the injured, a number of people standing in front of the car, one of them wears military trousers, pouring water on people, including a child, whose clothes have been removed. The last part of the video was filmed at a medical point where the logo of "Free Aleppo Doctors Association" can be seen on a wall inside the medical point as a number of people, including children, wear oxygen masks. filmed after the incident

column2: Evidence of planes dropping toxic gases produced by a Jordanian company
column3: The video contains testimony of a man who says he is a lawyer working for the Syrian Institute for Justice and Accountability. It also shows remnants of the ammunition allegedly used in the chemical attack, where the man says that "Al-Baha Company For Soda Industry" was written on the remnants of the ammunition in Arabic, as well as a caution that it contains gas in English. After searching in the internet on Al-Baha company, I found a site belonging to Al-Baha Company for producing soda and chlorine based in Jordan. It can be seen that the company's logo "BCC" is the same as that appears on the remnants of the ammunition: http://bcci-jo.com/index.php?option= com_content & view = featured & Itemid = 435 & lang = en. It is likely that the remnants of ammunition appeared in this video are the same as that shown in another video: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D0VCQMCvc28

column2: For the third time, bombing Al-Lataminah town with Chlorine gas
column3: The video begins from inside what looks to be a medical point, with footage for a woman whose face is not shown as she is provided with an oxygen mask, near her a person who seems to be a member of the medical team appears while he is moving a blue cylinder which seems to be containing oxygen. After that, a person wearing a medical uniform and a medical mask, he stands near one of the patients, and close to the person who appeared at the beginning of the video. Then a person in the medical uniform appears while wearing an oxygen mask on his face, and a blue cylinder can be seen near him. The video then continues with footage of two men putting blue cylinders in a car, and on their right, there is a wall with the word "chemical" written in orange. This wall is then fully filmed, where a paper can be seen on it, reads "The ambulance entrance", and a phrase in orange reads "Dangerous Area Chemical". The video contains testimony of a person wearing a blue T-shirt with the Civil Defense logo, what appears to be the remains of an explosive cylinder can be seen near him. During his testimony, the video includes footage of a child inside a medical point. The video then shows a white pickup truck, and a number of men seem to be members of the Civil Defense in agricultural land, where two of them take out some things from the truck, including a small yellow tube. Two members of the Civil Defense wear special suits that appear to be used to protect from the dangerous chemicals. Then they walk on agricultural land, one of them carries a black bag while the other carries a small sign with a warning symbol reads "dangerous". Then the video shows a yellow cylinder on the ground that appears to have been exploded. After that, an unnamed person gives testimony about the incident. The camera focuses on several metal pieces on the ground that look to be remnants of the ammunition allegedly used in the attack. The video ends with footage showing what appears to be a sample of soil placed in a transparent plastic bag.

column2: Bombing AL-Lataminah city with chemicals
column3: The video is a report of the Aleppo Today channel about the attack. It begins with footage of two people seem to be members of the Civil Defense team in special protective suits in agricultural land, one of them carries a black bag. Then the video shows metal pieces on dusty ground. After that, a person in medical uniform appears wearing an oxygen mask on his face in what looks to be a medical point. One of the Civil Defense elements appears again while collecting samples of the soil. The video continues with footage of a wall with a phrase written in orange on it, reads "Dangerous area, Lataminah the chemicals 25-3-201". From inside the medical point the video continues showing a child crying, a person appears while carrying a blue cylinder. The video then shows a white pickup truck, and a number of men seem to be members of the Civil Defense in agricultural land, where two of them take out some things from the truck, and one of them opens several bags, the word "equipment" can be read on one of them. Then a lying woman appears, she puts an oxygen mask on her face in a place looks to be a medical point. The video contains testimony of a person who was identified as Dr. Mahmoud Abbas Al-Mohammad - a general surgeon. The video then continues to show footage of two civil defense elements wearing self-contained breathing apparatus (SCBA) in agricultural land. Then a metal piece appears on dusty ground, and footage of the two people who appeared at the beginning of the video while collecting the samples standing near a sign reads "The Danger of Unexploded Weapons". It is worth mentioning that many of the footage in this video are contained in another video: https://cube.syrianarchive.org/littlefork/youtube_video/f1190c3475cf242478748a8013a1445cdb653cb419be4a50420c1fb7d8c7fbb1/8vIMxgQ0RI8.mp4

It also shows two men wearing medical masks on their faces are standing in a street, it was claimed they are taking samples from the collision site of the shell, which contains toxic chemicals. A small red sign on the ground reads "Danger of Unexploded Weapons" and another sign on the opposite side of the street reads "Do Jihad, your brothers the mujahidin" can be noticed. One of the two men testifies within the video. During his testimony, a pickup truck carrying a machine gun passes the street. A  hole can be seen near the person;  which is claimed to have been caused as a result of the collision of the chemical-laden shell. The other person, who was in the street, takes the body of a small bird out of a cage and puts it in a transparent plastic bag. A dead body of a white goat can also be seen. The video contains testimony of a person who was alleged to be a survivor of the chemical attack, which was filmed inside a house. The video continues to show footage of the city.

column2: Aerial filming of the impact site
column3: The video shows a crater in the road that was claimed to be where the sarin-laden rocket landed. Muaz al-Shami, a journalist, said in the video that the Syrian Sukhoi 22 fighter had thrown that missile at Khan Sheikhoun. The video also shows aerial top view footage of the place claimed to be the impact site. A number of injured people lying on the floor can be seen, including children who appear to be suffering from suffocation as water is sprayed on them. The video also shows civil defense members in a place close to what appears to be an explosion had occurred in. Muaz al-Shami appears in a place where he claims to have a civil defense center and a field hospital that was targeted by an airstrike. A pick-up car with a civil defense logo parked in an area with a trail of destruction can be seen. During the video, we can see what appears to be the targeted hospital as the trail of destruction can be seen. The video shows a number of victims, among them a person still under the rubble

column2: disprove the Syrian and Russian allegations, this is the claimed "chemical weapons factory" in Khan Sheikhoun
column3: The video shows the journalist Hadi al-Abdullah standing near a crater, which was claimed to be where the rocket used in the chemical attack landed. Then we can see aerial footage of the site; grain silos can be noticed next to the road where the impact site is. The camera goes with Hadi To the silos area to disprove Syrian regime and Russia's allegations, which says that they targeted the silos used by the armed opposition as a chemical weapons factory, according to Hadi's claim. The video shows an area where what appears to be grain silos has been destroyed. Hadi says that this silos area has been targeted and destroyed by the warplanes six months ago and became a cattle area, a body of a goat can be seen.
